Record management; version control system (VCS): GitHub
Deployment and continuous integration: Netlify
CSS for HTML: Bootstrap
For design: figma, zeplin, behance


::: Getting started with Git and Netlify :::

(1) If you don't have a GitHub, create a GitHub account https://github.com/signup

(2) Install GIT
    For Mac users,
    Make sure you have homebrew installed by running this code in Terminal, 
    /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
    then run, brew install git

    For Windows users,
    Install git here, https://git-scm.com/download/win 

    For Linux distribution users, https://git-scm.com/download/linux

    For both Mac and Windows, make sure git is installed by entering, git ,in the terminal (Mac OS) or Command Prompt (or GitBash for Windows)

(3) Open the Terminal (or Command Prompt on Windows)

(4) CD (change directory) to your folder in the terminal `cd folderpath/foldername'

(5) Enter this command to initialize git, git init (NOTE: DO THIS ONLY ONCE FOR THE FOLDER)

(6) Enter this command, git add .
    In case of email/username error, run
    git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
    git config --global user.name "Your Name"

(7) Enter this command, git commit -m "First Commit"

(8) Create a new repository on GitHub
    Follow the instructions to, â€¦or push an existing repository from the command line
        copy first line

(10) Enter this command, git push origin master

you do need to create an access token for GitHub
https://docs.github.com/en/github/authenticating-to-github/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/creating-a-personal-access-token

