-- Steps to Deploy on Netlify --

(1) Create an account on Netlify (https://www.netlify.com/).

(2) On the dashboard, click the button 'New Site from Git'.

(3) Choose 'GitHub' as your Git Provider.

(4) If prompted to grant permission to Netlify, please confirm.

(5) Choose 'Only select repositories' and select your repository from the list.
    If you are unable to see your repo, click the link that says 'Configure the Netlify app on GitHub'.
        In the configuration window, scroll to the section 'Repository Access'.

(6) In Netlify, click the name of your repository and the deployment will begin.

Notes about Git 
(1) If you've initialized in the wrong folder, toggle 'view hidden folders', and delete the .git folder. Repeat all the steps for Git.
(2) Always cd into the correct folder before running any shell command
(3) Use git init only once
(4) Use git add remote... only once
(5) If you've directly modified the repo on github.com, use git pull to sync the changes.


